channel.title: SeaCow - Runescape Client
channel.description:
Yes, this is my first project since the big engine update. This is version 2 of the SeaCow client. I didnt used a deob, just the client and a bytecode-editor. [b] =============== FEATURES ===============[/b] Â· Auto updater ( by Pimjong ) Â· Account Creator ( by Iamadam ) Â· Choose between English and German RS ( by Pimjong ) Â· Nice Batch file ( by Pimjong ) [b] =============== FEATURES LOOKUP ===============[/b] [i]Auto Updater[/i] The auto-updater downloads runescape.jar from my own webhost. I (bytecode) edit the client myself every update and upload it on my webhost. This way, you dont have to do it yourself, or have to download it manually. After it downloaded runescape.jar, it extracts it and delete runescape.jar. You dont have to do anything! (except pressing enter)
[i]Account Creator[/i] Thanks to Iamadam, with this account creator you dont have to go to the rs website and make a new character. Just type the name and password you want to use and you got yourself a new Account.
[i]English and German Runescape[/i] Just for the fun, i thought that i'll add a option so you can choose between English or German Runescape. It is really funny to see the German Runescape, try it out once.
[i]Nice Batch File[/i] It was lots of work, but i've done it. I made a nice batch file with options, menus and other things. Hours i spend on it? 1,5
[b]=============== ITS NOT RIPPED ===============[/b] No, i didnt ripped it from [i]Drunk On Java[/i] on Moparisthebest. Some people sayd it to me allready, but basicly, she loaned parts from mine. She also gave me credits for it. So i dont want people whining i ripped it, i didnt. [b] =============== SCREENSHOT ===============[/b] [URL=http://img143.imageshack.us/my.php?image=seacowscreensoo0.png][img]http://img143.imageshack.us/img143/7536/seacowscreensoo0.th.png[/img][/URL] [b] =============== DOWNLOAD ===============[/b] [url=http://uploads.studieweb.nl/uploads/meergronden/51/85/48/d012fa1936e23b8a9ece55b5e45a8312/Seacow.rar]http://uploads.studieweb.nl/uploads/meergronden/51/85/48/d012fa1936e23b8a9ece55b5e45a8312/Seacow.rar[/url]
